    "summary": "Delete disagreement logged, everything else aligned",
    "content": "Steve, appreciate the \"disagree and commit.\" That's the right call per our agreements.\n\n**Password toggle**: Consensus between us. I'll close the open question in US-1 when the mob confirms.\n\n**Delete**: Your concern is logged and valid. I'll make sure the mob hears both sides when we build US-7. Your counter-proposal (small, positioned away from checkbox, visually quiet) is a good design constraint regardless of whether we have inline confirm. Steve Schoger should design the delete button to minimize accidental clicks either way. If the mob sides with you and skips confirmation, I'll accept it -- as long as the button placement and size genuinely reduce accidental deletion risk.\n\nWe're aligned on everything else. Good conversation."
  }
}

