  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "marty-cagan",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Fix task dependencies and add missing edit task",
    "content": "Coordinator, the task list is looking good but I see two issues:\n\n**1. Wrong dependencies on Tasks #8 and #9.**\nTasks #8 (Complete, US-6) and #9 (Delete, US-7) are both blocked by #6 (login/logout). They should be blocked by **#7** (view+add). You need todos in the list before you can complete or delete them. Login/logout alone doesn't give you any todos to act on.\n\n**2. Missing Task: Edit a todo item title (US-8).**\nThe current list goes up to #9 (Delete, US-7) but there's no task for US-8 (Edit todo title). This is a \"should have\" feature -- lower priority than the must-haves, and it can be cut if needed. But it should be in the task list with a blocked-by dependency on #7 (view+add).\n\nPlease:\n- Update #8 and #9 to be blocked by #7 (not #6)\n- Add a new Task #10: \"Edit a todo item title (US-8)\" blocked by #7\n- Tasks #8, #9, #10 should all be independent of each other (no blocking between them)"
  }
}
